{
  "stem": "19198.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 303.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were just more isolated and probably had the-- the business shrunk to practically nothing.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that went on for almost two years after Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in the fall of 1940, all the Jews of the-- of the entire state were rounded up on a moment's notice.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And being able to take practically nothing were [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] put on trains.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But they were relatively civilized.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "The locked trains were-- were passenger trains.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they were on the train for some 40 or 48 hours.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they were dumped into the camp in Gurs, G-U-R-S, in the Pyrenees Mountains.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "A-- a terrible place which had originally been built for the refugees from the Spanish Civil War, and a place that had daily rain and where they-- they had to wade through mud most of the time.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But there they-- they were [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] almost abandoned, with-- with very little access to-- to food.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But it was not a concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "They were able to get out of the camp to-- for errands and so on.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "So they-- and the most important thing, they were able to receive mail, both letters and packages, which we-- packages we sent constantly.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And also, we doubled our efforts to get visa and-- and immigration for them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Being a citizen by that time, I was able to give the visa-- give the-- the-- what do you call it?",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The guarantee for the visa, which meant that they would have a much higher priority than if a stranger had-- alone had given it.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I couldn't give it alone because my income wasn't sufficient.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I gave it together with a family of good friends.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
